---
title: Grilled Dill-Garlic Double Salmon Salad with Ranch Dressing and DIY Croutons
description: It's family BBQ time and this dish let's everyone build their plates with what they love! Drizzle delicious ranch over everything and prepare for compliments from everyone in your home.

Ingredients: Salmon fillets • Cucumber • Spring mix (lolla rosa multi-leaf lettuce, red flash red oak lettuce, red leaf multi-leaf lettuce, green oak lettuce, bally hoo tango lettuce) • Roma tomatoes • Ciabatta roll (unbleached untreated enriched wheat flour flour (wheat flour, niacin, reduced iron, thiamine mononitrate, riboflavin, folic acid), water, sea salt, yeast, malted barley flour) (barley, wheat) • Ranch dressing (canola and/or soya oil, buttermilk (partly skimmed milk, salt, bacterial culture), white vinegar, water, sugar, salt, frozen egg yolk, spices, polysorbate 60, xanthan gum, natural flavour, monosodium glutamate, lactic acid, sodium benzoate, calcium lactate, calcium disodium EDTA) (egg, milk) • White wine vinegar (wine vinegar, potassium metabisulfite) (sulphites) • Garlic salt (salt, garlic powder, silicon dioxide) • Dill-garlic spice blend (dehydrated onion, dehydrated garlic, salt, dill weed, canola oil, silicon dioxide) (sulphites).

